<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-280-132  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 280 132.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronics Weekly  May 3 1989 n1459 p40(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Vallance attacks Labour's BT plan. (British TelecommunicationsChmn Iain Vallance)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wilson, Richard; Turner, Mark.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>British Telecommunications Chmn Iain Vallance attacked the Laborparty's plans to nationalize the telecommunications giant.andO;Vallance said there is no logic in Labor's claim that publicownership is necessary in order to create a national broadbandfiber optic network, estimated to cost 20 billion pounds sterling.andO;What is needed is the proper regulatory approach, Vallance said,referring to restrictions in British Telecom's license thatprevent it from integrating telephone and television services onany broadband network.andP;  The company has no incentive to invest inthe network under such restrictions.andP;  The Thatcher government saidit has no plans to insist that British Telecom go ahead with theinvestment in the fiber optic network.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   British Telecommunications PLC (officials and employees).andO;Topic:     TelecommunicationsBroadbandFiber OpticsExecutiveOwnershipPolicyLabor Party (Great Britain).andO;Person:    Vallance, Iain (attitudes).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>